Sharing your data can make your IKEA app feel more like home. See what kinds of information we collect and why, then manage your data preferences below. You can always come back later if you’d like to make changes.

This data is used by IKEA to personalise and tailor your experience. Allows use of behavioural data, using cookies and other technologies, to improve and provide relevant content on IKEA platforms and in communications.

This data allows us to count visits and traffic sources so we can measure and improve the app performance. It helps us know which sections are the most and least popular, and see how people move around the app. All information is used in aggregated form and we won’t try to specifically identify you from it.
Allows sharing of behavioural data with advertising partners. This data is used to enhance and report on the personalised advertising experience on partner sites.

This data is necessary for the app to function, and it can’t be switched off in our systems. Your settings like region and language are stored locally in the app. This data is also collected when you request services, like setting your privacy preferences, logging in or filling in forms. We never store any personally identifiable information.

Online co-worker discount applies to all IKEA products except for gift cards, delivery and administration fees. The discount can be used only for the purchase of goods for yourself, your spouse/partner and children living in your home and/or for children living away from home who are financially dependent on you (students). Goods purchased with the co-worker discount are not allowed to be bought with the purpose of reselling them.\10\10Max. amount for co-worker discount is 500 EUR per calendar year.\10\10Trainees, external co-workers and IKEA co-workers with contract of three months or less are not eligible for the co-worker discount.\10\10Read the full co-worker discount policy on ico-worker

Your personal data can only be used if there’s a good reason for it. Some of the laws call that a “legal basis.” In this app, we use multiple legal bases depending on the type of data processed and the context. We use consent for providing personalized content, accessing your location, camera and calendar, as well as sending you marketing communications. We use legitimate interest for doing analytics to make the app better and to understand your needs. If you shop through the app or make an account, we’ll process your data on the basis of contract.
Your data belongs to you. That’s why we want you to see exactly what kinds of data we can collect and what we do with it.
We collect personal data you share with us, like your name, email address, delivery address, phone number, and purchasing activity.

When you use a mobile device or tablet to browse and shop, we track how you interact with the app, using data like device information and ID. This helps us do several things, including making the app more useful for you.

When you use the app, we ask you to provide us with access to certain information from your device, like location (to know your delivery options) or camera (to scan products with your app). You can manage the app permissions in the app settings.

IMPORTANT - UPDATE before release We are IKEA Limited (company number: 01986283) (“IKEA”) and our registered address is 7th Floor 100 Avebury Boulevard MILTON KEYNES MK9 1FH. IKEA is the “data controller” of any personal data it may collect, process and hold about you, unless we inform you otherwise.\10\10Address: IKEA, Customer Support Centre, Kingston Park, Peterborough, PE2 9ET, UnitedKingdom.\10\10Phone: 0203 645 0000.\10\10Email:dataprivacy.cookies.gb@ikea.com.
What data we collect and why
Sharing your data shouldn’t make you uncomfortable. Think of it as a two-way conversation between you and us. The more we get to know you, the more personalized your IKEA experience becomes.
We need some of your personal data to provide you with the products and services you request or purchase from us.
Make our products and services available

If you adjust your settings to allow personalization, you’ll notice a new experience on your inspirational home feed. As you search, browse, and buy new things, the feed will adapt to fit your style.\10\10If you create an account, you’ll be able to access and save your favorites across all your devices and save your address for an easier shopping experience. Plus, if you opt in for marketing communications, we can keep you updated with our latest news and offers.
Your personal data can also help us keep improving our products and services. For example, we want to make sure our website is customer-friendly and always works properly.
Sometimes we have to keep your data to comply with legal obligations, such as tax reporting.
What we do with your data
Here’s how you benefit (hint: it’s all good news)

We take the security of your personal data very seriously and we do our best to protect it. For example, our encryption techniques, firewalls, and password protection ensure that your data is protected.\10\10We keep your personal data as long as necessary, or until you ask us to delete it. These timings vary based on the type of data and why we have to keep it in the first place.

We will never sell any of your personal data to a third party. However, to provide you with our services, we share your personal data with our trusted third party service providers and our group companies and our franchisor, Inter IKEA Group. For example, our delivery provider needs your data to make sure your order arrives on time and in good shape.

We are a global company, so we may sometimes need to transfer your personal data to one of our group companies or suppliers located in other parts of the world. When we do, we use legal safeguards to protect your data.
We believe everyone deserves to feel at home online. So we prioritize protecting your personal data.
Here’s how your data stays safe and secure

We’ve said it before and we’ll say it again: your data belongs to you. So we try our best to give you the choice about what you share. When we ask you to provide specific data, we’ll explain why we’re asking for it. For example, we might ask for your location when you’re checking out because we want to make sure the items you want are available.\10\10We’ve also created account controls so you can learn more about your data. This is the place to go if you want to read more about specific kinds of data we collect or see the updated privacy policy. And as we continue offering more and more personalization throughout the app, this section will become even more useful for you.\10\10You have the right to access your data, get it corrected if it’s wrong, and opt out of marketing communications.\10\10If you decide it’s time to say goodbye for good, you can simply delete your account. All of your account information will be erased, with the exception of data we are required to keep for legal reasons like tax reporting.

You can read more about your rights, including the circumstances in which they apply, in the IKEA KOREA Privacy policy under my info→about the app→Privacy Policy. You also have the right to complain or inquire about our use of personal data to the following authorities and organizations:\10Personal Information Dispute Mediation Committee (www.kopico.go.kr / 1833-6972 without area code)\10Personal Information Protection Center (privacy.kisa.or.kr / 118 without area code)\10Cyber Division, the Ministry of Scientific Investigation at the Supreme Prosecutors’ Office (www.spo.go.kr / 1301 without area code)\10Cyber Bureau at the National Policy Agency (ecrm.cyber.go.kr/ 182 without area code)
Everyone has the right to control their personal data. So we make it easy for you to adjust your preferences whenever you want—or even delete your account entirely.
And here’s how to be the boss of your data
